page.text: Status of Traffic Evaluation Related to Corrective Action at Glenview Landfill Site
Provisional Decision – Provisional Approval – Transmittal Number X260852
This letter has been prepared by Langdon Environmental LLC (Langdon) on behalf of Charter
Environmental Inc. (Charter) to provide a status of the evaluation of traffic along Drum Hill Road and
Westford Street between Route 3 and the entrance to the Glenview Landfill closure project.
The traffic evaluation was agreed to be performed by Charter in response to comments from the
Town of Chelmsford on the Interim Stockpile Plan permit that was issued by your office on April 25,
2014. The general approach of the evaluation was presented to the attendees at the public
informational meeting held on June 4, 2014. At this meeting, there was a request to evaluate
alternative routes that could potentially reduce traffic along Drum Hill Road.
To obtain background data prior to the commencement of the closure project, a traffic engineer from
Green International Affiliates, Inc. (Green) collected traffic counts from Drum Hill Road in early June.
These counts found that average daily volumes of 23,000 vehicles per day on Drum Hill Road between
the Route 3 interchange and Parkhurst Avenue. A copy of the traffic counts package is attached to
this letter. Green has also conducted an initial field review of the route and evaluated the operating
At a meeting with representatives of the Town on June 26, 2014 immediately after the
commencement of grading and shaping material deliveries, the scope of work and completion
schedule for the traffic evaluation was discussed. Based on input from the Town, it was agreed that
the final evaluation should be delayed until after the summer vacation season so that the results can
reflect peak conditions. Green intends on finalizing their field work and evaluation during September
and present a written report on their findings in October. At that time, Charter will schedule a public
informational session to present and discuss the findings.
In addition to the traffic evaluation, Charter has diligently enforced the specified traffic route during
the initial operations including installation of a camera that monitors the site entrance. To date, only
a single truck route issue has been identified and that related to a truck that entered the driveway
from the wrong direction. This driver was reprimanded and can no longer make deliveries to the
Please do not hesitate to contact me at my office at (508) 630-0351 or mobile phone at (617) 875-
3693 if you have any questions or require anything further.
